Author: vetuklepe
Title: [ANN][ICO]Emiba - high-profitable synthesis of diamond raw
Body: Friends, today we will talk about the benefits of rough diamonds in medicine. üîª Magnetic resonance imaging is one of the most effective ways to diagnose various diseases as it allows to obtain a layer-by-layer image of the internal organs. üîª However, because expensive superconducting magnets are used in MRI devices, this procedure is not for everyone, as many clinics cannot afford to purchase such equipment. The handling of diamonds in medicine will solve not only the problem of accessibility but many others. Such a solution is presented by American experts from the National Academy of Lawrence in Berkeley who conducted a series of experiments. üîª How do gem-based technologies work in medicine? Scientists decided to use tiny crystals in MRI devices, through which the green light of a laser beam transmitted and the minerals exposed to a weak magnetic field at the same time. Thanks to this approach, it was possible to increase the polarization of the spins hundreds of times and thus improve the quality of the resulting image. üîª The team leader noted that no one had previously achieved such results to confirms the revolutionism of the invention. Scientific language discovery is called the effect of the hyperinflation of nano and microscale diamonds. In the future, it can transform the market of not only magnetic resonance but also nuclear tomographs. üîª What practical advantages does the invention have? The scientific component is essential, but technology in medicine can bring practical benefits. If we talk about the use of diamonds in MRI, they provide: ‚Ä¢ cost reduction; expensive superconducting magnets are not used; ‚Ä¢ increase the accuracy of diagnosis; able to create the most detailed image of the internal organs; ‚Ä¢ downsizing is especially vital as modern MRI devices occupy entire rooms. üîª The procedure will become more accessible and accurate, which will contribute to improving the level of medical care. Title: [ANN][ICO]Emiba - high-profitable synthesis of diamond raw
Body: The two most important days in your life are the day you are born and the day you find out why. Mark Twain Hi! First, I would like to thank everybody who interested in our project, asked questions, and supported us. I should begin to say about us, but the main thing to present our project is our mission and philosophy. The mission determines our goals, the philosophy determines our way. We have a dream. We got the dream when we began to work for the project, and this dream is our mission and is our light in dark tunnel. We have just seen it for a moment, but the light was so bright and clear to blind us. Emiba gave us a knowledge of human development and the way of reaching it. Now we know what we can give people, what we can give humanity. I do not want to tell you about diamonds and other perspective materials, I just want to share with you our ideas. The team of the project knows what we must do for realizing our plans and reaching the aims. We try to do it without mistakes and problems, but these mistakes and problems are just stones on our way, just the reasons to stumble and to rise up again. These reasons are the most important things in the life of the project. The efforts, the trials, the ways of development of yourself lead to the goal steps by step. Having a dream is not only the possibility, but it is also the necessity. Sometimes the logic tells us that it is impossible. However, if we want to reach our inadequate dream, we have to be inadequate, and not to stop. We have to be crazy about our project because it is our obsession.  We do everything we must. If we needed change, we changed. If we needed development, we developed. If we needed to be creative, we become creative. It is our sacrifice to feel all blows of the fate to the project. When we step into our fears and continue to push ourselves to go on something happens for us. We became stronger, more courage, and we get our dream more closely. Some people convince us that what we are doing does not have any value and we will give up on our dream. I hear it from my close people sometimes. However, I just know they make a mistake. I must learn how to tune out the critics outside and the critic inside. We have a power, a spirit to develop the project from the beginning until the end. And we know we will face defeat again and again without giving up. It is just a progress of the project and we exactly know what we want. Best regards, Daniil Voloshin, CEO
